    "description": "Classification of drill actions using the MLC to detect idle, screw, drilling or percussive drilling states.\n\nThis system provides an example of classifying specific actions rather than simple vibrations, enabling the detection of the operating modes of a common household power drill: screwing, drilling, and percussive drilling, or not moving. Since motion recognition can be very specific, you can also clone this project to retrain it and tailor it to a different drill.\nTo use this example, affix the board firmly to the top side of the drill. Remember that vibrations may dislodge the board, and that classification is better the more firmly it is secured to the machine.",
